\fs36 \cf0 What This Is\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 A browser-based multiplayer tank combat game rendered on top of Google's Photorealistic 3D Tiles. Players pick a real city, drop into the streets in a tank, and fight other players. Buildings act as walls and cover. No install, no account \'97 just a URL.\
The reference point for the rendering approach is {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://fly.alistairmcleay.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 fly.alistairmcleay.com}}, a browser flight simulator using CesiumJS + Google 3D Tiles. This project uses the same visual foundation but replaces flight physics with ground-vehicle physics and adds combat.\
