\f0\b \cf0 1.4 \'97 Building Collision (OSM Layer)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 This is the critical engineering problem. The 3D tiles are visual only \'97 they have no physics mesh you can collide against efficiently for a ground vehicle.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Approach: OSM building footprints as 2D collision polygons
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 When a city/arena is selected, query Overpass API for all building footprints in the bounding box:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 [out:json][timeout:25];\
way["building"](\{\{bbox\}\});\
out geom;\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Convert the returned polygon coordinates to Cartesian (CesiumJS world coordinates)\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Store as a spatial index (e.g., a simple grid hash or quadtree) for fast point-in-polygon / line-segment-intersection queries\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 On each frame, before moving the tank:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Project the tank's intended new position\
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Check if the new position falls inside any building polygon\
\ls5\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 If yes, slide along the building edge (wall sliding) or simply block movement\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 For better feel, give the tank a collision radius (~3-5m) and check circle-vs-polygon intersection\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Known limitation:
\f1\b0  OSM footprints and Google 3D tile geometry won't perfectly align. Buildings may appear slightly offset from their collision boundary. This is acceptable for an MVP. Players will learn the feel quickly. The alternative \'97 raycasting against the 3D tile mesh every frame for a ground vehicle \'97 is too expensive and unreliable (LOD pops, mesh gaps).\

\f0\b Optimization:
\f1\b0  Pre-fetch and cache building footprints per arena. Don't query Overpass per session \'97 query once at build time or on first load, then cache the GeoJSON.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

